I have this strange problem that when i save javascript files and reload my web page the page has a javascript error, for example 'unexpected end of input', this then gives the line and file of the error in Chrome dev tools.
When i use Chrome dev tools to inspect the file with the error i can see that a small snippet from the end of my javascript appears to have been duplicated and popped in randomly afterwards.

I've pasted example code below.
This can happen in multiple files and it always appears that it is the last part of my javascript that is duplicated and stuck in at the end of the file.

If i close down VS Code and reopen it i can see the duplicate code in the .js file. If i remove this from the file and save, the web page still has the error. Re-opening VS Code again still shows the code in the file, despite me removing it.

I have tried disabling all the extensions i use and the issue still occurs.
If i roll back to version 1.20.1 the issue goes away.

I'm not entirely sure what the problem is.

